observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Management to:

Serve written reminders/notices to officers and employees with outstanding cash advances and require the concerned officers and employees who are still in service to immediately liquidate their cash advances, otherwise, suspension of salaries shall be imposed until the same have been fully settled and liquidated;
Request that outstanding cash advances of deceased officers and employees be written off in accordance with the applicable provisions of COA Circular 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016;
Increase the Fidelity Bond of the Accountable Officers in accordance with the Bureau of Treasury Circular No. 02-2009 dated August 6, 2009;
Submit to the Audit Team a certified copy of the transmittal of liquidation of the Confidential/Intelligence Funds; and
Discontinue the practice of allowing additional cash advances to those Officials and Employees with outstanding accounts.
Henceforth, the Municipal Mayor should strictly enforce the rules and regulations on the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances prescribed in the COA Circular 97-002 dated February 10, 1997.
